  "text": "Morphology of CHA Nanorods TEM was used to characterize morphology and size of synthesized nanorods. Figure 1a shows that the synthesized HA nanorods have lengths of 60-90 nm and widths of 10-20 nm, which is similar to the size of human apatite crystals [CITATION_1] . As carbonate content increase (Fig. 1a-d) , the lengths of nanorods decrease and the widths slightly increase. The SEAD patterns shows multi-crystalline electron diffraction concentrate rings attributed to (002), (300), (310), and (211) crystallographic planes of hydroxyapatite [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
